Let's imitate dumb people
and talk about TV.

14:10.171 --> 14:12.539
Well, I just finished
re-watching "Breaking Bad."

14:12.541 --> 14:14.241
Have you seen it?

14:14.243 --> 14:15.642
Of course.

14:15.644 --> 14:17.344
And I definitely think it's a good thing

14:17.346 --> 14:19.346
we nerds came along and made watching TV

14:19.348 --> 14:20.714
feel more like books.

14:23.051 --> 14:25.152
Hello, all. I'm your waitress.

14:25.154 --> 14:28.289
I'm just trying to balance
work and pursuing my dreams.

14:28.291 --> 14:29.790
And your drinks on my tray, of course,

14:29.792 --> 14:33.160
because again, I'm a waitress.

14:33.162 --> 14:34.228
Hi, waitress.

14:34.230 --> 14:36.730
We were just talking
about "Breaking Bad."

14:36.732 --> 14:38.332
Oh, you were in here
the other day saying

14:38.334 --> 14:39.533
that you love "Breaking Bad."

14:39.535 --> 14:41.569
I believe your exact words were:

14:41.571 --> 14:43.437
"Finally a show where
people respect the power

14:43.439 --> 14:45.639
and majesty of chemistry."

14:45.641 --> 14:47.975
Oh, I totally agree. I
loved every second of it.

14:47.977 --> 14:49.743
Well, except for the "Fly"
episode, of course.

14:49.745 --> 14:50.978
Ugh, totally.

14:50.980 --> 14:52.313
Are you kidding me?

14:52.315 --> 14:53.881
The "Fly" episode was a
daring deconstruction

14:53.883 --> 14:54.848
of the show's form,

14:54.850 --> 14:55.883
boiling complex issues down

14:55.885 --> 14:58.152
to a single primal drive.

14:58.154 --> 15:00.554
Really? I think you mean boring.

15:00.556 --> 15:03.724
Boring? I think you're
confusing boring with nuance.

15:03.726 --> 15:05.025
I think you're confusing nuance

15:05.027 --> 15:06.660
with masturbatory filmmaking.

15:06.662 --> 15:10.831
Well, sure it's masturbatory,
but isn't that pleasurable too?

15:10.833 --> 15:12.299
TouchÃ©.

15:15.837 --> 15:16.870
Why, thank you.

15:16.872 --> 15:19.106
Uh, what's happening here?

15:19.108 --> 15:20.708
I mean, seriously, random waitress,

15:20.710 --> 15:22.209
you're poaching my date?

15:22.211 --> 15:24.178
What are you talking about?
We're just talking.

15:24.180 --> 15:25.512
Don't play dumb with me.

15:25.514 --> 15:27.681
That's a game you'll never win.

15:30.418 --> 15:31.685
I wasn't going to say anything,

15:31.687 --> 15:33.120
but now that you're being weird,

15:33.122 --> 15:35.656
obviously this is the way
this story was going to end.

15:35.658 --> 15:37.324
I told her what to say.

15:37.326 --> 15:39.860
It's a classic Cyrano-inspired
Comic-Con Rom-Com.

15:39.862 --> 15:42.863
"Blah, blah, blah, blah,
blah, blah, I'm Shea."

15:42.865 --> 15:44.331
Do you really think we live in a world

15:44.333 --> 15:46.100
where brains are going
to trump sex appeal?

15:46.102 --> 15:48.135
I hope we live in that world.

15:48.137 --> 15:49.603
And clearly this is a man who respects

15:49.605 --> 15:51.538
intelligence and substance.

15:51.540 --> 15:52.673
Hold on a second.

15:52.675 --> 15:55.175
Am I being fought over
by two beautiful women?

15:57.879 --> 16:00.180
This is a new experience.

16:00.182 --> 16:01.882
Although, throughout the animal kingdom,

16:01.884 --> 16:03.417
it's not uncommon for a desirable male

16:03.419 --> 16:06.186
to have more than one mate.

16:06.188 --> 16:08.355
Dude, are you trying
to work a threesome?

16:08.357 --> 16:10.991
Am I? I'm really new at this.

16:12.294 --> 16:16.230
I mean, the... the concept
sounds great, but...

16:16.232 --> 16:17.765
I have enough anxiety with one woman.

16:17.767 --> 16:20.501
I don't think being
outnumbered would help.

16:20.503 --> 16:22.202
You have anxiety?

16:22.204 --> 16:23.871
Generalized, social, or panic disorder?

16:23.873 --> 16:24.838
All of them.

16:24.840 --> 16:26.740
Me too. What do you do for it?

16:26.742 --> 16:29.243
I... I've tried yoga but I don't like...

16:29.245 --> 16:31.478
Being told how to breathe.

16:31.480 --> 16:33.380
You finished my sentence.

16:33.382 --> 16:34.615
No girls has ever done that before.

16:34.617 --> 16:36.717
Okay, you're right.

16:36.719 --> 16:38.419
This is how this ends.

16:38.421 --> 16:41.155
I don't understand all this
talking about stuff anyway.

16:41.157 --> 16:43.624
What are your thoughts on this?
What are your thoughts on that?

16:43.626 --> 16:45.259
Just shut up and feel me up already.

16:51.200 --> 16:52.666
Wait, so now you think the prison guy

16:52.668 --> 16:54.001
didn't do the glue thing?

16:54.003 --> 16:55.102
Then who did? I don't know,

16:55.104 --> 16:57.571
but it's making me crazy.

16:57.573 --> 16:59.974
So how did it go with Kyle?

16:59.976 --> 17:01.108
He still says he didn't do it.

17:01.110 --> 17:02.109
I guess I believe him.

17:02.111 --> 17:03.978
Well, let that be the end of it.

17:03.980 --> 17:06.747
- No, no, no.
- Kenny Robinson.

17:06.749 --> 17:09.183
He ate glue, so I know he had it.

17:09.185 --> 17:11.919
Mike, you promised you'd
let this thing go.

17:11.921 --> 17:14.722
Let's just find out where Kenny
lives and stake him out.

17:14.723 --> 17:16.390
I'll bring the black coffee, and you...

17:16.392 --> 17:17.892
Mike, damn it, stop!

17:17.894 --> 17:20.661
No good ever comes from people
digging into their pasts.

17:20.663 --> 17:23.396
My whole career, but go on.

17:24.366 --> 17:26.233
- Just let it go.
- Why?

17:26.234 --> 17:27.568
- Because I said so.
- Why?

17:27.569 --> 17:29.770
Because Kyle did it, okay?

17:29.772 --> 17:33.540
The glue, the chair, the whole thing.

17:33.542 --> 17:36.644
You knew all along, and
you didn't say anything.

17:36.646 --> 17:38.279
Wow, this is some "Pretty Little Liars"

17:38.281 --> 17:39.947
going on here.

17:42.563 --> 17:44.730
I can't believe this.
You knew Kyle did it.

17:45.037 --> 17:46.879
The school called that day
and asked if I wanted

17:46.904 --> 17:48.338
to make a formal complaint,

17:48.372 --> 17:49.572
and I said to forget about it.

17:49.607 --> 17:51.241
- Stella...
- Yeah, I know the drill.

17:51.275 --> 17:52.709
You guys are gonna yell at each other.

17:52.743 --> 17:55.678
Let me know who wins.
Good night, Grandpa.

17:55.713 --> 17:57.914
Good night, honey. Sweet dreams.

17:57.948 --> 17:59.883
What the hell are you
gonna yell at me for?

17:59.917 --> 18:01.985
Because you knew about this
and you didn't tell me!

18:02.019 --> 18:04.487
Because you could have
protected me and you didn't!

18:04.522 --> 18:06.589
I was protecting you.

18:06.624 --> 18:08.758
If people knew you got
Kyle into trouble,

18:08.793 --> 18:11.027
you would have turned into that kid,

18:11.062 --> 18:13.663
and that kid gets beat up every day.

18:13.698 --> 18:16.132
So instead, I signed you
up for boxing lessons.

18:16.167 --> 18:19.536
Where I got beat up every day.

18:19.570 --> 18:22.505
But you stuck with it, and
you got big and strong.

18:22.540 --> 18:24.774
- So you're welcome.
- You want me to thank you?

18:24.809 --> 18:26.509
Because what I did made you stronger.

18:26.544 --> 18:29.345
But to get there you let me
feel humiliated and alone.

18:29.380 --> 18:30.680
Do you ever stop whining?

18:30.715 --> 18:32.082
Do you ever stop being a mean old prick?

18:32.116 --> 18:33.550
This is great!

18:33.584 --> 18:35.018
Not now, Martina.

18:35.052 --> 18:36.519
See how alike you two are?

18:36.554 --> 18:38.388
Don't say that!

18:39.924 --> 18:41.658
What's great is that
we're finally getting

18:41.692 --> 18:43.927
at the core issues.

18:43.961 --> 18:47.263
Honey, you want to pretend that
time in your life never existed,

18:47.298 --> 18:51.101
you want some apology that's
gonna make it all seem better,

18:51.135 --> 18:53.870
but the way to truly put it behind you

18:53.904 --> 18:56.473
is to embrace what that time taught you

18:56.507 --> 18:59.109
and love that scared
little boy inside you.

18:59.143 --> 19:00.477
I don't love that little boy.

19:00.511 --> 19:03.279
That's why there are no
pictures of that little boy.

19:05.616 --> 19:06.716
There is one.

19:08.819 --> 19:11.388
I've had it since you were 11.

19:11.422 --> 19:14.624
I keep it in my wallet.

19:14.658 --> 19:16.826
Why?

19:16.861 --> 19:18.995
Because I did love that little boy.

19:21.165 --> 19:22.465
Dad...

19:22.500 --> 19:23.900
Look...

19:23.934 --> 19:25.935
maybe I made some mistakes,

19:25.970 --> 19:28.671
and what I did could have turned
out badly for a lot of kids,

19:28.706 --> 19:29.906
but not you!

19:29.940 --> 19:31.841
I mean, look how good you turned out.

19:31.876 --> 19:35.412
And that's on you.

19:35.446 --> 19:40.216
I guess in your... your own strange way,

19:40.251 --> 19:44.387
I know you were looking
out for me, so...

19:44.422 --> 19:46.356
All right, I accept your apology.

19:46.390 --> 19:48.425
I didn't apologize.

19:51.128 --> 19:52.529
Yes, you did.

19:55.332 --> 19:58.768
So you don't have to deny it anymore.

19:58.803 --> 20:00.270
You did it.

20:00.304 --> 20:03.640
I kind of did.

20:03.674 --> 20:05.642
Well, I'm a grown man,

20:05.676 --> 20:07.911
and revenge is ultimately unsatisfying,

20:07.945 --> 20:09.245
so I only ask one thing, Kyle.

20:09.280 --> 20:11.848
Buy me a beer.

20:11.882 --> 20:13.416
Happy to do it, buddy.

20:21.926 --> 20:24.194
You glued me to the chair, didn't you?

20:24.228 --> 20:26.963
- I kind of did.

20:28.866 --> 20:30.267
Revenge is ultimately unsatisfying,

20:30.301 --> 20:33.136
but it's still fun.

20:33.170 --> 20:36.172
You just lost yourself a
free beer, my friend!

20:38.008 --> 20:39.376
Today would have been a terrific day

20:39.410 --> 20:41.578
to wear underwear.

20:44.849 --> 20:47.684
All right, people, prepare
yourself for a show

20:47.718 --> 20:50.453
my last girlfriend called...

20:50.488 --> 20:52.055
adequate.

